SPEC FOLLOWUP OF REAL TRANSIENTS.  IN FACT, ONE MIGHT ARGUE THAT SINCE 
THE 60 SEC IS MAINLY DRIVEN BY THAT, WE SHOULD MINIMIZE THE FALSE ALARM 
RATE DUE TO MOVING OBJECTS INCLUDING DEBRIS:
  Will LSST provide a limited-capability event broker, as described in
x2.4.2? The SRD seems to demand it, but the opposing view is that
it's not clear how useful it would be (and it's not useful, we shouldn't
waste resources to provide it).
